Key Match Events: Botswana secured a 1-0 victory over Cape Verde with Sesinyi scoring in the 52nd minute.
Key players for Botswana included Johnson, Ramotse, Seakanyeng, and Kebatho who were all notable in the match.
Arcanjo from Cape Verde received a yellow card in the 70th minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Botswana and Cape Verde were set to clash in the second of their October double-header for the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers.
Botswana aimed to secure consecutive wins and move into second place in Group C.
Cape Verde sought to bounce back from a defeat and improve their standing in the qualifiers.
